div><div class="_9lQcE"><div class="eDfJP undefined">Americans are quitting their jobs at record rates. That has big implications for the economy.</div></div></div></a></div><a class="" href="/guides/"><span class="_9Iyu1 _4tXYb aLRIE">More guides</span></a></aside><div class="_9OiHk"><div class="_2KLGz"><div class="_9BANw"><h2 class="_6t8Fn">Support journalism with a mission.</h2><button class="_9Zp9w" type="button" title="Close"><svg width="11px" height="11px" viewBox="0 0 11 11" aria-hidden="true" class="_7geTk"><path fill="var(--color,#000)" d="M10.911 1.321L9.68.09 5.5 4.27 1.32.088.09 1.32l4.18 4.18L.09 9.68l1.232 1.231 4.18-4.18 4.178 4.18 1.231-1.232L6.732 5.5z"></path></svg><span>Close</span></button><video autoplay="" class="f0sbC alignleft medium" controls="" muted="" playsinline="" poster="" preload="auto" src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/MBB-Final-360-1.mp4"></video><div class="aOW2p"><p class="cyhZ9">We believe our reporting will help you make better choices that result in better businesses, better leadership, and a better global economy. Support our purposeful journalism with a <a href="https://qz.com/subscribe/email/">free seven-day trial</a>.</p></div><hr class="_44APO"/><form class="_8xL_9"><p class="_1gCtl">Get the Quartz Daily Brief in your inbox each morning.</p><div class="_4hGdw"><div class="_7O0vU"><div class="f9Sdm"><div class="_5RuH1"><div class="_9Xjy-"><input type="email" class="_1adIN email" id="email-signup-daily-brief" placeholder="Enter your email" value="" aria-invalid="false"/></div></div></div></div><div class="dIcJg"><button class="_6i3Tp aLRIE" type="submit"><span class="_9Iyu1 NhZKo aLRIE"><span class="az84-">Sign me up</span></span></button></div></div><p class="d9te0">By providing your email, you agree to the <a class="" href="/about/privacy-policy/">Quartz Privacy Policy</a>.</p></form></div></div><hr/><p class="ejHOm donXX" aria-hidden="true"> </p><div class="_1UpnV"><figure class="B8yJE"><div class="_1sHFm"><div class="_57zR9 _1ZFNs visible" style="padding-bottom:56.367924528301884%"><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/womanworkingfromhomewithcat.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=239&amp;crop=1" srcSet="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/womanworkingfromhomewithcat.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=239&amp;crop=1 424w, https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/womanworkingfromhomewithcat.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=848&amp;h=478&amp;crop=1 848w, https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/womanworkingfromhomewithcat.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=820&amp;h=462&amp;crop=1 820w, https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/womanworkingfromhomewithcat.jpg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1640&amp;h=924&amp;crop=1 1640w" sizes="(min-width: 48em) 820px, 424px" alt="woman works from home while a cat looks at her on the computer keyboard" class="" decoding="async"/></div><span class="_1PgFp"><span class="fGOw-">Image copyright: </span><span>Reuters/Eva Plevier</span></span></div><figcaption class="_1EKE2">Home sweet home.</figcaption></figure></div><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">6 Quartz stories we really liked</h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">🏢 It’s in the <strong>best interests of employees’ psychological well-being</strong> to <a href="https://qz.com/work/2045471/the-psychological-case-for-delaying-office-reopenings/">delay office reopenings</a>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">🦄 <strong>India</strong> has its <a href="https://qz.com/india/2045269/indian-crypto-unicorn-coindcx-gets-funds-from-facebooks-saverin/">first cryptocurrency unicorn</a>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">😔 <a href="https://qz.com/africa/2045986/social-media-covert-sales-behind-kenyas-skin-lightening-growth/">No one will talk about</a> Kenya’s <strong>booming skin-lightening business</strong>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">💼 There is <strong>no such thing</strong> as a <a href="https://qz.com/2046486/there-is-no-such-thing-as-a-low-skilled-worker/">low-skilled worker</a>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">🎓 Beijing’s <a href="https://qz.com/2045981/chinas-clampdown-on-tutoring-upends-the-lives-of-millions/">private-tutoring crackdown</a> is <strong>upending lives in China</strong>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">💰 Hackers are <a href="https://qz.com/2046192/hackers-are-returning-the-spoils-of-the-poly-network-crypto-heist/">returning the spoils</a> of the <strong>world’s largest crypto heist</strong>.</p><form class="_8xL_9"><p class="_1gCtl">📬 Kick off each morning with coffee and the Daily Brief (BYO coffee).</p><div class="_4hGdw"><div class="_7O0vU"><div class="f9Sdm"><div class="_5RuH1"><div class="_9Xjy-"><input type="email" class="_1adIN email" id="email-signup-daily-brief" placeholder="Enter your email" value="" aria-invalid="false"/></div></div></div></div><div class="dIcJg"><button class="_6i3Tp aLRIE" type="submit"><span class="_9Iyu1 NhZKo aLRIE"><span class="az84-">Sign me up</span></span></button></div></div><p class="d9te0">By providing your email, you agree to the <a class="" href="/about/privacy-policy/">Quartz Privacy Policy</a>.</p></form></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">Visualizing the IPCC report</h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">The most important takeaways from the 4,000-page Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change report released this week are <a href="https://qz.com/2044235/ipcc-report-can-we-limit-climate-change-and-extreme-weather/">easily summarized</a>. Global warming is caused by human greenhouse gas emissions, and the impacts range from very bad to catastrophic.</p><p class="cyhZ9">While much of it is written in inscrutable scientific jargon, if you want to understand the scientific case for man-made global warming, look no further. We’ve reviewed the data, summarized the main points, and created an interactive graphic showing a “heat map” of <a href="https://qz.com/2044219/the-2021-ipcc-report-shows-high-confidence-in-climate-science/">scientists’ confidence</a> in their conclusions. The terms describing statistical confidence range from very high confidence (a 9 out of 10 chance) to very low confidence (a 1 in 10 chance). Check out <a href="https://qz.com/2043894/what-does-the-ipcc-say-about-climate-change/">our full visualization</a>.</p><div class="_7mwZR"><figure class="B8yJE"><div class="_1sHFm"><div class="_57zR9" style="padding-bottom:52.35849056603774%"><noscript><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/ipcc-confidence_002.gif?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=222&amp;crop=1" alt="A gif of the Quartz IPCC chart visualization tool that shows paragraphs color coded and then zooms into one."/></noscript></div></div></figure></div></div><div class="aOCxk inline-slot dCnqM"><div><div id="ad-1"></div></div></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">How to learn something new online</h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">Sure, you could just fire up YouTube, but adding a bit of structure can make the difference between a few idly wasted hours and a truly transformative experience.</p><p class="cyhZ9">1️⃣ <strong>Decide why you want to learn this thing</strong>, and write that motivation down.</p><p class="cyhZ9">2️⃣ <strong>Set a goal for yourself</strong>. Be specific about what you want to achieve and when, breaking long-term goals into smaller chunks.</p><p class="cyhZ9">Setting the goal is the easy part; the rest of our <a href="https://qz.com/emails/quartz-how-to/2042515/">member-exclusive How To email</a> can help you achieve the rest.</p><p class="_7Orpu">Becoming a member directly supports the work we do and gives you access to every bit of it.</p><a class="" href="/subscribe/email/"><span class="_9Iyu1 NhZKo aLRIE">✨ Become a Quartz member ✨</span></a></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">Charting the US labor shortage</h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">The US unemployment rate declined from 5.9% to 5.4% in July (though it is still higher than the 3.5% unemployment rate pre-pandemic). However, a closer look at the trends in worker movement by the sizes of companies reveals the <a href="https://qz.com/2044074/small-businesses-are-bearing-the-brunt-of-the-us-labor-shortage/">disparity between small businesses and larger ones</a>.</p><p class="cyhZ9">Data from June show workers are quitting at historic levels, but it’s hitting small businesses much harder. There are also more job openings at companies with over 250 employees, and hiring is increasing faster at large businesses.</p><div class="_1UP0V medium"><iframe class="bbngu" id="datawrapper-chart-Vuvl1" src="https://datawrapper.dwcdn.net/Vuvl1/6/" scrolling="no" height="388"></iframe></div></div><div class="aOCxk inline-slot dCnqM"><div><div id="ad-2"></div></div></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">Imagery interlude</h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">The NASA Inspector General <a href="https://oig.nasa.gov/docs/IG-21-025.pdf">said this week</a> that despite $420 million spent since 2008, NASA will not have two suits ready for a 2024 moon landing. The total price tag will be over $1 billion, more than what it cost to build the Falcon 9 orbital rocket and cargo Dragon spacecraft, as former SpaceX engine guru Tom Mueller <a href="https://twitter.com/lrocket/status/1425212338240512001">observed</a>. (Actually, per NASA, it cost $850 million, $396 million of which came from SpaceX.) Naturally, Elon Musk <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1425100482779942936">offered to step in</a> and build a suit for the space agency. </p><p class="cyhZ9">Tim Fernholz has more on the US government’s farfetched plan to <a href="https://qz.com/2046840/a-1-billion-space-suit-is-holding-up-nasas-2024-moon-landing/">return astronauts to the moon by 2024</a>—and why the delay is about more than just space suits. </p><p class="cyhZ9">In the meantime, here’s former NASA administrator Jim Bridenstine high-fiving engineer Kristine Davis, who is wearing a prototype of NASA’s lunar space suit, the <a href="https://www.space.com/nasa-unveils-xemu-moon-spacesuit-orion-suit-unveiled.html">Exploration Extravehicular Mobility Unit</a> (xEMU).</p><div class="_7mwZR"><figure class="B8yJE"><div class="_1sHFm"><div class="_57zR9" style="padding-bottom:56.367924528301884%"><noscript><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/NHQ201910150006_large-e1628778157351.jpeg?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=239&amp;crop=1" alt="NASA Administrator Jim Bridenstine, left, high fives Kristine Davis, a spacesuit engineer at NASA’s Johnson Space Center, wearing a ground prototype of NASA’s new Exploration Extravehicular Mobility Unit (xEMU), during a demonstration of the suit, Tuesday, Oct. 15, 2019 at NASA Headquarters in Washington. The xEMU suit improves on the suits previous worn on the Moon during the Apollo era and those currently in use for spacewalks outside the International Space Station and will be worn by first woman and next man as they explore the Moon as part of the agency’s Artemis program."/></noscript></div><span class="_1PgFp"><span class="fGOw-">Image copyright: </span><span>NASA/Joel Kowsky</span></span></div><figcaption class="_1EKE2">You&#x27;ll like the way you look. I guarantee it.</figcaption></figure></div></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS">We’re obsessed with TV intros</h3></div><div class="_7mwZR"><figure class="B8yJE"><div class="_1sHFm"><div class="_57zR9" style="padding-bottom:76.17924528301886%"><noscript><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/giphy-1-1.gif?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=323&amp;crop=1" alt="An animated gif from the opening credits of The Simpsons, in which the characters pop up from holes in the floor and couch while a giant mallet tries to smack them down, like a giant game of whack a mole."/></noscript></div><span class="_1PgFp"><span class="fGOw-">Image copyright: </span><span>Giphy</span></span></div></figure></div><p class="cyhZ9"><strong>Always there for you.</strong> The television opening title sequence is as old as the medium itself—older, in fact. It’s evolved alongside advancements in filmmaking technology and changing TV norms, from characters awkwardly smiling through the camera into our souls to zany animated sequences that have little to do with the show you’re about to watch. No matter the form or style, TV intros remain a key part of the viewing ritual—even if you’re now able to skip them with the press of a button, thanks to streaming. The show is about to begin; <a href="https://qz.com/emails/quartz-obsession/2045787/">let the Quartz Weekly Obsession cue it up for you</a>.</p><form class="_8xL_9"><p class="_1gCtl">📬 Want to escape the news cycle? Try our Weekly Obsession.</p><div class="_4hGdw"><div class="_7O0vU"><div class="f9Sdm"><div class="_5RuH1"><div class="_9Xjy-"><input type="email" class="_1adIN email" id="email-signup-quartz-obsession" placeholder="Enter your email" value="" aria-invalid="false"/></div></div></div></div><div class="dIcJg"><button class="_6i3Tp aLRIE" type="submit"><span class="_9Iyu1 NhZKo aLRIE"><span class="az84-">Sign me up</span></span></button></div></div><p class="d9te0">By providing your email, you agree to the <a class="" href="/about/privacy-policy/">Quartz Privacy Policy</a>.</p></form></div><div class="aOCxk inline-slot dCnqM"><div><div id="ad-3"></div></div></div><hr class="hr"/><div class="_3j-bl"><div class="_9eZVq"><h3 class="nTSJS"></h3></div><p class="cyhZ9">Now that you’ve made it through our homepage introduction, find the next episode in <a href="https://qz.com/latest/">Quartz’s latest</a>. </p><div class="_7mwZR"><figure class="B8yJE"><div class="_1sHFm"><div class="_57zR9" style="padding-bottom:63.679245283018865%"><noscript><img src="https://cms.qz.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/30-rock-kenneth-show-must-go-onward.gif?quality=75&amp;strip=all&amp;w=424&amp;h=270