[],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"dateModified","value":"1628881054"}],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qSXdORGN6TmpVPXww","innerHtml":"The NASA Inspector General \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Foig.nasa.gov\u002Fdocs\u002FIG-21-025.pdf\"\u003Esaid this week\u003C\u002Fa\u003E that despite $420 million spent since 2008, NASA will not have two suits ready for a 2024 moon landing. The total price tag will be over $1 billion, more than what it cost to build the Falcon 9 orbital rocket and cargo Dragon spacecraft, as former SpaceX engine guru Tom Mueller \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Ftwitter.com\u002Flrocket\u002Fstatus\u002F1425212338240512001\"\u003Eobserved\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. (Actually, per NASA, it cost $850 million, $396 million of which came from SpaceX.) Naturally, Elon Musk \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Ftwitter.com\u002Felonmusk\u002Fstatus\u002F1425100482779942936\"\u003Eoffered to step in\u003C\u002Fa\u003E and build a suit for the space agency. ","tagName":"p","type":"CORE_PARAGRAPH"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qSXdORGN6TmpVPXwy":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"dateModified","value":"1628881250"}],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qSXdORGN6TmpVPXwy","innerHtml":"Tim Fernholz has more on the US government’s farfetched plan to \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fqz.com\u002F2046840\u002Fa-1-billion-space-suit-is-holding-up-nasas-2024-moon-landing\u002F\"\u003Ereturn astronauts to the moon by 2024\u003C\u002Fa\u003E—and why the delay is about more than just space suits. ","tagName":"p","type":"CORE_PARAGRAPH"},"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qSXdORGN6TmpVPXw0":{"__typename":"Block","connections":[],"attributes":[{"__typename":"Attribute","name":"dateModified","value":"1628881181"}],"id":"YmxvY2s6Ym5Wbk9qSXdORGN6TmpVPXw0","innerHtml":"In the meantime, here’s former NASA administrator Jim Bridenstine high-fiving engineer Kristine Davis, who is wearing a prototype of NASA’s lunar space suit, the \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.space.co